Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.02,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Opening}
Comment: 0,0:01:29.99,0:01:30.03,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Part A}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.54,0:01:51.22,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Do you remember our conversation\N about creating a world where curses no longer exist? {about eliminating cursed spirits from the world}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.72,0:02:00.06,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Regardless of which method is pursued,\N it means advancing humanity to the next stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.64,0:02:05.77,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, I need to buy time for Larue to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.69,0:02:13.15,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,The next stage of humanity\N lies in breaking away from cursed energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.20,0:02:18.41,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,No. It lies in optimizing cursed energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.66,0:02:26.42,Default,Yuji,0,0,0,,Uh, I don't understand either of those. {crazy how cr got it wrong but perry was right, somewhat}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.00,0:02:32.92,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I thought you gave up on that plan\N twelve years ago when Zenin Toji died. {wtf back to back cr Ls}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.92,0:02:36.09,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,That's what I told Geto{**-kun}, yes. {"I was talking to Geto, you know." implies that from his response she's somehow able to deduce that he's not geto, which doesn't make sense since she did say she's looking at the alternate approach. the meaning here is "That's just what i told Geto." Though the anime then decides to zoom in on his forehead cut which is in line with the previous translation, but the manga doesn't have this scene so... did the animators misunderstand the meaning of this line?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.05,0:02:38.68,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Well, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.64,0:02:41.85,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I went back to my original idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.85,0:02:45.69,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Besides, there's one big flaw in your optimization plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.69,0:02:51.32,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Extremely few sorcerers and curses\N emerge outside of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.36,0:02:57.45,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Tengen's barrier is indispensable \Nto your optimization plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.62,0:03:00.74,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,And using Tengen {to optimize cursed energy }would mean
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.74,0:03:06.08,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,the only ones capable of becoming sorcerers\N would be the humans of this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.96,0:03:11.50,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Japan would practically \Nhave a monopoly on cursed energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.17,0:03:16.59,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,No country, especially a certain superpower,\N would stand by and allow that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.22,0:03:24.02,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,If flesh-and-blood humans become a source of energy,\N it's easy to imagine the suffering that would bring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.52,0:03:30.52,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,That is a world far removed from the ideal I pursue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.82,0:03:34.15,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,And what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:37.41,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Our objectives are not the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.99,0:03:43.16,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,What I pursue is not a world without\N cursed spirits nor any sort of idyllic peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.54,0:03:46.79,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Non-sorcerers, sorcerers, cursed spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.79,0:03:52.55,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Those are all possibilities for \Nthe shape of cursed energy that is mankind. {oof}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.38,0:03:58.55,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,And yet, I feel there must be more to it than that. {Though that shouldn't be anywhere near the full extent.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.05,0:04:03.93,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I tried to give rise to other possibilities\N for mankind on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.94,0:04:10.61,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,But it didn't work out. {failure.gif}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.61,0:04:15.19,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\pos(955.8,1020)}What I can create is limited\N by the bounds of my own potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.90,0:04:21.57,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,What I wanted was always \h\Nglimmering in the darkness of chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.91,0:04:23.33,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.33,0:04:28.41,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\pos(959.4,1020)}What I should have created\N was chaos that went beyond my own control.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.08,0:04:32.42,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I just finished extracting the technique for it. {so he was also stalling this whole time? just like yuki? just like me? that's genius!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.75,0:04:36.76,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,There was a cursed spirit called Mahito, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.76,0:04:39.30,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,The one whose technique could manipulate souls!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.30,0:04:41.05,Default,Yuji,0,0,0,,That guy just absorbed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.05,0:04:42.35,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.93,0:04:46.89,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Idle Transfiguration.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.79,0:05:12.71,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Tengen's barrier? No, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.71,0:05:15.34,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Remote activation of a cursed technique?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.59,0:05:18.92,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You have my thanks, Itadori Yuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.42,0:05:27.31,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,A cursed spirit's mastery of their technique ceases to progress\N the moment they're absorbed by Curse Manipulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.31,0:05:30.31,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Mahito truly matured through his fight with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:35.77,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I actually wanted to have Jogo as well, but no matter. {another perry L}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.52,0:05:38.15,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,What did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.57,0:05:44.66,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I remotely activated Idle Transfiguration on two types\N of non-sorcerers that I had marked ahead of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:14.06,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,The ones like Itadori Yuji,\N whom I had absorb cursed objects. {oh no no no that's not the finger he's talking about here, nope}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.81,0:06:21.57,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,And the ones like Yoshino Junpei,\Nwho have cursed techniques but not the brains of a sorcerer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.57,0:06:25.32,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I've adjusted their brains to match those of sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.87,0:06:28.45,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,To the former, I gave strength as vessels.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.45,0:06:32.58,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,To the latter, the ability to use their techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.04,0:06:35.12,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,And finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.59,0:06:42.34,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,As of this moment, I've released the seal\N on those cursed objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.13,0:06:48.47,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\pos(970,1020)}Some were left bedridden\N due to my cursed energy when I marked them, {both cr and perry took Ls for this line}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:50.72,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\pos(970,1020)}but they will soon awaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.81,0:06:58.02,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,In order to deepen their understanding of cursed energy,\NI'll have them kill each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.65,0:07:01.78,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,They're all carefully hand-picked by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.78,0:07:06.66,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Think of it as unleashing a thousand \Nmalevolent Itadori Yujis. {???}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.37,0:07:10.70,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,A thousand? That's not too many.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.70,0:07:13.87,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,You're underestimating human rationality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.87,0:07:18.38,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Do you think people will start killing each other\N just because they were granted power?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.38,0:07:21.25,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,There's an order to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.25,0:07:24.97,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I would not make such an obvious oversight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.55,0:07:27.89,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You're asking pointless questions now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.01,0:07:33.56,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,He's pissing me off. Let's all gang up on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.56,0:07:35.89,Default,Yuji,0,0,0,,Sorry, I can't move right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.44,0:07:44.61,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Uraume?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.94,0:07:48.36,Default,Uraume,0,0,0,,{\i1}I regenerated my body with reverse cursed technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.36,0:07:49.24,Default,Uraume,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.62,0:07:50.49,Default,Uraume,0,0,0,,Poison?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.41,0:07:55.25,Default,Choso,0,0,0,,My blood got mixed with yours \Nthrough Piercing Blood. Of course it's poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.87,0:07:58.75,Default,Momo,0,0,0,,Wait, we're not getting cover from Mai{**-chan}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.75,0:08:01.25,Default,Momo,0,0,0,,There may still be more of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.67,0:08:08.09,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,My ally is protecting Aoi,\N the girl with the gun, and the suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.09,0:08:09.39,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,They don't belong here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.72,0:08:11.35,Default,Panda,0,0,0,,Can you move?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.35,0:08:12.30,Default,Kamo,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.30,0:08:14.85,Default,Kamo,0,0,0,,I can regulate my body temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.85,0:08:15.89,Default,Kamo,0,0,0,,No problems here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.94,0:08:20.15,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,I'm so done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.65,0:08:22.65,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I wasn't done talking. {yap technique}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.32,0:08:25.44,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\q2}These cursed objects are what's left of {that i provided}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:30.66,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\q2}the sorcerers with whom I painstakingly forged \NBinding Vows over a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.66,0:08:35.33,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,And it wasn't just sorcerers \Nthat I formed Binding Vows with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.25,0:08:41.79,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Although they were annulled when I obtained this body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.67,0:08:44.80,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:49.93,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,This is the world of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.81,0:09:43.48,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,See you later, Itadori Yuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.82,0:09:48.11,Default,Yuji,0,0,0,,{*}Mr. Gojo{*Gojo-sensei}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.99,0:09:53.74,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I expect great things from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:57.99,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Are you listening, Sukuna? It's beginning once again. {Italics?} {this is def not _spoken_ dialogue. it's also not an internal thought even tho it looks like it. it's actually something like the narrator, something above the usual speech bubbles, so no italics}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.29,0:10:01.75,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,The world of Heian.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.37,0:10:06.17,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,The Golden Age of Sorcery!
Comment: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:15.05,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Part B}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.02,0:10:28.69,Default,Announcer,0,0,0,,{\an8}The following was recorded by our crew,\N who happened to be on-site
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.69,0:10:33.36,Default,Announcer,0,0,0,,{\an8}reporting on another matter \Nat the time of the incident in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.36,0:10:35.03,Default,Announcer,0,0,0,,{\an8}Please have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.45,0:10:40.70,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}So it's been about ten minutes since the blackout.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:45.88,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}The blackout continues and the cause remains unknown. {the text on screen says govt has declared that this is caused by cursed spirits but the reporter says she doesn't know what's going on?} {this isn't live footage, it was recorded previously by the aforementioned crew} {istg i saw a sign that said it's LIVE though} {okay... so during that scene it was LIVE at that time, i.e. last night, this is the next day}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.88,0:10:49.50,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}We still can't contact the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.50,0:10:53.67,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}We have practically no idea what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.04,0:10:44.33,Default,OldMan,0,0,0,,Looks like something {\i1}real{\i0} crazy is going down!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.33,0:10:45.88,Default,Granny,0,0,0,,Are you sure it's not fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.88,0:10:48.59,Default,Oldman,0,0,0,,It's all over the news!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.00,0:10:52.80,Default,Granny,0,0,0,,I'll be out late today, so microwave something for dinner. {ah yes frozen dinner my favourite}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.80,0:10:54.34,Default,Oldman,0,0,0,,{\pos(1111,1020)}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.68,0:10:57.55,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,All 23 wards are nearly wiped out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.55,0:11:01.72,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,The safety of the Prime Minister's office,\N including the Chief Cabinet Secretary, remains uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.72,0:11:05.98,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,It's a political void! A literal void!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.48,0:11:11.40,Default,Staff(Male),0,0,0,,Even by the lowest estimate, we're looking at a plan\N to evacuate at least five million citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.40,0:11:14.99,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,All the love hotels, campgrounds,\N and abandoned settlements.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.99,0:11:19.28,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,Use whatever is available, as long as it has\N the bare minimum infrastructure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.28,0:11:22.87,Default,Staff(Female),0,0,0,,More importantly, how are we supposed\N to explain this to the residents?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.87,0:11:25.87,Default,Staff(Male),0,0,0,,No point announcing anything\N when we don't even know the cause!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.54,0:11:30.38,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}Furthermore, the government has yet to make a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.38,0:11:32.88,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}Is it simply a substation malfunction?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.88,0:11:34.55,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}Is it a terrorist attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.55,0:11:38.84,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}Or perhaps it's due to a natural disaster,\N like an earthquake? {if it was an earthquake you would FEEL it maybe?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.84,0:11:41.64,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}Either way, the cause remains unclear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.64,0:11:43.81,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}All we can do is wait while they uncover it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.13,0:11:39.30,Default,Man,0,0,0,,All the conspiracy theorists are crawling out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.30,0:11:41.64,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,Can you put your phone down \Nand give me a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.64,0:11:43.81,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.14,0:11:52.48,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,The only places confirmed to be safe are parts of Okutama, Ome, Akiruno, Hachioji, Machida, and a few islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.48,0:11:54.11,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Safe for now, you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.11,0:11:57.20,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,The number of cursed spirits unleashed\N is no less than ten million.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:12:00.70,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,You want to enact an evacuation order\N on every ward of the entire city?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.70,0:12:03.12,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,After that, we declare the wards forbidden to entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.12,0:12:05.37,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,Make it a real uninhabited zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.37,0:12:08.87,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,And what about the announcement? Who's making it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.87,0:12:11.88,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Less "who" and more "how" to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.88,0:12:14.38,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,We still can't get a hold of the deputy secretary?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.84,0:12:17.55,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,No, unfortunately not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.55,0:12:19.84,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,I haven't heard from his secretary, either. {secretary's secretary? okay}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.05,0:12:24.35,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,What do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.35,0:12:27.85,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Calm down. The upper brass will figure something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.85,0:12:31.86,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,We just need to establish contact with each ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.19,0:12:34.69,Default,Boyfriend,0,0,0,,Yen's straight up tanking! {The low yen ain't stopping.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.69,0:12:36.99,Default,Girlfriend,0,0,0,,Isn't that good for exports, at least?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.36,0:12:39.11,Default,Staff(Male),0,0,0,,The Japanese Business Federation has lost it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.11,0:12:42.49,Default,Staff(Female),0,0,0,,They won't be doing any lobbying if everyone's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.03,0:12:45.37,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Relocate government functions to Osaka! {this is less about moving the person and more about moving the house of power to osaka, just like old times}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.37,0:12:48.87,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,At this rate, there'll be a massive outbreak\N of cursed spirits everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.87,0:12:52.25,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Sorcerers have already been dispatched\N to protect evacuees in the city!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.25,0:12:53.59,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,The outbreak is coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.59,0:12:57.72,Default,Official(Female),0,0,0,,With a power vacuum of this scale,\N there could be foreign military intervention!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.72,0:12:58.59,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.59,0:12:59.43,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.43,0:13:00.38,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.38,0:13:01.39,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.47,0:13:03.39,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.10,0:13:08.60,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,They're going to disclose the existence\N of cursed spirits to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:09.60,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:11.73,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,They're going public with cursed spirits?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.73,0:13:13.19,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Are they serious?! {Have they lost their minds?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.19,0:13:17.40,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Apparently, they intend to announce that\N cursed spirits only appear in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.40,0:13:23.49,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,So the goal is to direct the populace's leaking \Ncursed energy to Tokyo and limit the outbreak, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.49,0:13:27.91,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,This is why I recommended Itami as a potential\N relocation site after Kansai Airport was built!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:30.21,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,Maybe it's better this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.21,0:13:33.83,Default,Official(Male),0,0,0,,It wouldn't have come to this\N if the bureaucracy was functioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.59,0:13:39.84,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}So we are once again sharing the latest. {this scene is in fact the latest and shows live footage}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.84,0:13:44.39,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}The blackout still continues,\N and we're unable to contact anyone. {so they can't contact anyone but live broadcast works huh?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:48.60,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}There's been no official announcement either, \Nso the cause remains unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.60,0:13:50.85,Default,Reporter,0,0,0,,{\an8}The question is, how long will this{\fscx180}—{\fscx}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.11,0:13:59.36,Default,Cameraman,0,0,0,,{\an8}What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.36,0:14:01.07,Default,Cameraman,0,0,0,,{\an8}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.07,0:14:02.15,Default,Cameraman,0,0,0,,{\an8}Fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.08,0:14:16.84,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.84,0:14:18.09,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,Some movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.63,0:14:25.26,Default,ImperialDirector,0,0,0,,The barrier around the Imperial Palace,\N rebuilt during the Meiji era.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:30.81,Default,ImperialDirector,0,0,0,,The barrier above the Tombs of the Star,\N a site once proposed for the capital in the Bakumatsu era.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.81,0:14:34.65,Default,ImperialDirector,0,0,0,,Force the expansion of the two barriers\N to the borders of the prefecture. {this part is tough, the history lesson was completely unnecessary}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.42,0:15:43.63,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.09,0:15:45.42,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.88,0:15:47.76,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,It's dangerous here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.44,0:15:59.90,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,I have a warm bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.15,0:16:07.61,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,I can sing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.66,0:16:15.41,Default,Girl,0,0,0,,What about my mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.96,0:16:20.54,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,Your mom and dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.54,0:16:24.84,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,your sister, brother, \Nand your teacher are all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.67,0:16:30.22,Default,Girl,0,0,0,,I don't have a brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.22,0:16:32.05,Default,Girl,0,0,0,,And I hate my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.05,0:16:36.14,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,I don't have a brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.14,0:16:40.60,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,And I hate my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:44.57,Default,Girl,0,0,0,,Are you okay? Need a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.57,0:16:52.57,Cursed,Woman,0,0,0,,Give me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.15,0:17:28.07,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.78,0:17:31.15,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Did I scare you? {this has a nice double meaning for us viewers as "scare" is interchangeable with "surprise" here}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.07,0:17:35.08,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:40.12,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Is someone with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.46,0:17:43.71,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Like your mom or dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.17,0:17:46.38,Default,Girl,0,0,0,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.55,0:17:49.97,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's all commercial buildings in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.97,0:17:51.68,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,{\i1}I doubt she's from around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.34,0:17:54.85,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Did you walk a lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.31,0:18:01.06,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I see, well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.90,0:18:10.86,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,You can see them, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.99,0:18:14.28,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Easy there, Rika{**-chan}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.32,0:18:16.66,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,You're going overboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.95,0:18:21.12,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I hesitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.87,0:18:27.96,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,The situation had reached a point \Nwhere I thought it best to just watch from afar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.17,0:18:33.59,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I'm sure you've noticed,\N but I'm not really on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.43,0:18:39.47,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I'm just a humble beauty who wants to\N eradicate curses from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.77,0:18:43.06,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It might not be much of an apology,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.06,0:18:48.69,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,but my allies and I will take responsibility\N for delivering the kids who were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.40,0:18:54.78,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It's high time I confronted Tengen, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.91,0:19:00.58,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.63,0:19:09.46,Default,Leader,0,0,0,,Good work, Okkotsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.46,0:19:11.80,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I'm not here for hollow praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.80,0:19:13.76,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Let's get to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:19.22,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Now you know that I'll obey your orders, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:25.48,Default,Leader,0,0,0,,No amount of killing cursed spirits will prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.73,0:19:29.61,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Then set up a Binding Vow or whatever you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.40,0:19:33.19,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I don't care if he's one of {*}Mr. Gojo{*Gojo-sensei}'s students.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.53,0:19:38.66,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,He cut off Inumaki{**-kun}'s arms in Shibuya. {> off screen}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.28,0:19:44.54,Default,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I will kill Itadori Yuji myself.
Comment: 0,0:22:10.02,0:22:10.06,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Ending}
